<b>Subject:</b> Good idea-As an alternative only though.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1242" TARGET=_self>PvP Server - Geiger</A> (Evildog)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> If we cannot get a PvP sever in final, how about a server that

<BR>&gt; defaults to PvP and allows -PvP as a turn in the note option.??
<BR>&gt; That way we can see if people would leave the flag at the
<BR>&gt; default. Call it a "control" group test. Make it so
<BR>&gt; that you can't go back to +PvP after you turn it in on this
<BR>&gt; special server.
<P>My understanding is that there WILL be a +PvP server in the final. So why bother with a switch at all on that server? If, however the developers where leaning away from said server (which seems VERY unlikely based on the <a href="http://eq.stratics.com/'>Poll</a> alone) your suggestion is really cool.
<P>Just my 2 Copper anyhow.
<P>-Gray
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
